Jaguar Land Rover Plans $8.2 Billion Quality Boost, FT Reports

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-05-06T00:28:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-06/jaguar-land-rover-plans-8-2-billion-quality-boost-ft-reports.html
Tata Motors Ltd. (TTMT) ’s Jaguar  Land Rover 
will spend 5 billion pounds ($8.2 billion) on product
development and new equipment at its three U.K. plants over the
next five years in a bid to improve quality levels to match its
German competitors,  Bayerische Motoren Werke AG (BMW) ,  Daimler AG (DAI) ’s
Mercedes-Benz and  Volkswagen AG (VOW) ’s Audi, the Financial Times
reported, without attribution.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 